PN,44801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,FIn 2016, Enniskillen teacher, Sally
OL,6,FRees was told news which changed her
OL,7,Flife. She was told that over a period
OL,8,Fof 14 months, she and another female
OL,9,Fteacher had been covertly filmed by a
OL,10,Fstudent who she knew and had taught
OL,11,Ffor years.
OL,13,FThat crime didn't even have a
OL,14,Fdefinition at the time. Now we know it
OL,15,Fwas upskirting. The dynamic of Sally
OL,16,Fbeing an adult of authority was
OL,17,Fcompletely turned on its head by this
OL,18,Fheinous violation.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,F"For me the big shock was being called
OL,6,Fa victim because I have never
OL,7,Fassociated myself with that word," she
OL,8,Ftold me in the latest Going the Extra
OL,9,FMile podcast.
OL,11,F"Within the first five or 10 minutes
OL,12,Fof being told, that's how the police
OL,13,Fofficer described me and that really
OL,14,Fjust shattered myself and who I was.
OL,16,F"I felt so humiliated and degraded and
OL,17,Fmy whole sense of safety in the
OL,18,Fenvironment of my workplace which had
OL,19,Fbeen a place of joy. I loved my job
OL,20,Fbut it became a place of fear."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,FThat moment which rocked Sally's
OL,6,Fworld, put her on a journey where she
OL,7,Fsought justice for what had happened
OL,8,Fand ultimately ended up changing the
OL,9,Flaw around the crime of upskirting.
OL,11,F"Back in 2016, we didn't even have the
OL,12,Fphrase upskirting to describe what had
OL,13,Fbeen done to us. Technology assisted
OL,14,Fabuse wasn't seen as abuse.
OL,16,F"If you can film up a teacher's skirt
OL,17,Fand there's no consequences for you,
OL,18,Fwhat are you actually saying to the
OL,19,Fwomen and girls in this school about
OL,20,Fhow they can expect to be treated?
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,F"But also what are you saying to boys
OL,6,Fand men about how they can treat women
OL,7,Fand girls? I didn't want it to happen
OL,8,Fto anybody else. During the process of
OL,9,Fthe judicial review, myself and my
OL,10,Fcolleague saw the extent of the
OL,11,Foffending which had been minimised
OL,12,Fboth by schools and by the law."
OL,14,FSally's drive for justice has led her
OL,15,Fto speak out on women's rights and
OL,16,Frelated issues. One of her interviews
OL,17,Fended up in the Louis Theroux Netflix
OL,18,Fdocumentary 'Inside the Manosphere'
OL,19,Fwhere the issue of toxic masculinity
OL,20,Fwas explored.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,FIronically they didn't ask permission
OL,6,Fto use the clip. They didn't have to
OL,7,Fbut for me I think
OL,9,F"It highlighted that key issue, the
OL,10,Fobjectification of women but also back
OL,11,Fto that issue that there's only one
OL,12,Fway to show up to be a man and it's
OL,13,Fthat idea that we're making
OL,14,Fmasculinity and femininity very binary.
OL,16,F"What happens to the people who are in
OL,17,Fthe gaps there and don't fit in? How
OL,18,Fare we supporting people to understand
OL,19,Fwho they are in the world and their
OL,20,Fsense of belonging?
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,F"With the Manosphere documentary, I
OL,6,Fthought it was fascinating,
OL,7,Fterrifying. I think it was brilliant
OL,8,Fthat it created this conversation
OL,9,Faround it but I also think it missed
OL,10,Fan opportunity.
OL,12,F"What it needed was that final section
OL,13,Fto show what these are the harm in the
OL,14,Freal life of these types of attitudes."
OL,16,FFor Sally, she feels that when it
OL,17,Fcomes to issues like violence against
OL,18,Fwomen and girls and domestic violence,
OL,19,Fmen need to come forward and talk
OL,20,Fopenly.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776423773
OL,3,C'How I made upskirting a crime'
OL,5,F"We need to bring men into the
OL,6,Fconversation because it's not a
OL,7,Fwomen's problem. It's women who are
OL,8,Fending up being the victims, who are
OL,9,Ffacing this abuse, who are losing
OL,10,Ftheir lives and in the majority of
OL,11,Fcases that is being committed by men.
OL,13,F"So this is a men's problem and they
OL,14,Fneed to be part of the conversation.
OL,15,FIf you're a man who is not doing that
OL,16,Fbehaviour, then you have a
OL,17,Fresponsibility to ensure that other
OL,18,Fmen that you know or are in your
OL,19,Fenvironment are not committing acts of
OL,20,Fviolence against women or the
OL,21,Fbehaviours where that starts.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
